 not being completely serious. One always, in fact, has a choice about whether or not to take seriously something that is supposed to be so. As a consequence, seriousness depends on different kinds of formalization or stylized practice. Styles of seriousness matter, Connor shows, because human beings are incapable of simply and spontaneously existing. Being a human means having to take seriously one's style of being.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSeriousness in literature. 0aSeriousnessxPhilosophy. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Modern / General .2bisacsh  aimportance.  aintention.  aperformance.  aremorse.  asolemnity.  astyle.  awarning.  azeal.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079132740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363687340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503636873423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503636873/original  a978-3-11-079132-7  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles